def: A stimulant, restorative, or tonic; a bracer. [Colloq.]
Infected or spotted with measles, as pork.-- Mea"sled*ness, n.
One who underwrites his name to the conditions of an insurancepolicy, especially of a marine policy; an insurer.
The act of setting forth ostentatiously; a boastful display.[Obs.] B. Jonson.
Chemistry considered with reference to the space relations ofatoms.
Like or pertaining to the genus Mullus, which includes thesurmullet, or red mullet.
Without an author; without authority; anonymous.
An indolent, encysted tumor of the skin; especially, asebaceous cyst.
